  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok so it's unfortunately due to a limitation in the engine. The reason is that the stats on which we rely on are computed on the 1000 first hits. In your example, we compute that on the secondary query without filters. The problem is that without filter and the limit of 1000 hits we end up with smaller values.\r\n\r\nWe could improve this behaviour by taking the overall max and mins of all the queries.",
